              "text": "•\nLangGraph and CrewAI are examples of frameworks that support these ideas using graphs, workflows, tasks, roles, and state.\nSource diagram - Slide 14: cognitive loop\nHow to read it: The loop cycles through perceive/interpret, reason/decide, act, and learn/update around a goal/context/task objective. The central goal gives\ndirection; memory and feedback make the process adaptive.\nCognitive loop\nPerceive -> Reason -> Plan -> Act -> Learn\nRepeat until the goal is reached, the task fails, or a stopping rule is met.\nPhase\nWhat it does\nSlide example\nPerception\nCaptures user input, API output, sensors, or\nexternal system data and structures it.\nmessage, timestamp, user_id, session_state,\nsentiment\nReasoning\nInterprets the perceived data: intent, priority,\nmeaning, why it matters.\nclassify_intent; determine_priority using sentiment\nand history\nPlanning\nTurns reasoning into a sequence of tasks/actions\nwith priorities.\nbilling_issue -> fetch_account_details ->\nanalyze_billing_history -> generate_explanation ->\noffer_resolution\nAction\nExecutes through tools, APIs, databases, function\ncalls, or other agents.\nbilling_api.get_account; llm.generate_response\nLearning\nMeasures outcome and updates\nmemory/preferences/models.\nsuccess_score; update_user_preferences; flag low\nsuccess\nCorrection / slide note: Slide 17 code appears truncated: it returns {\"context\": percep}, but the variable is incomplete. The intended idea is to\nreturn reasoning context based on perception data.",
