              "id": "ai-ml-agentic-ai-t07-c02",
              "title": "7.1 PerceptionModule",
              "page": 23,
              "text": "memory, episodic list, procedural dict.\nCognitiveAgent\nIntegrates all modules into a full loop.\nprocess_input, _create_tools, _generate_response,\nreflect_on_experience.\n7.1 PerceptionModule\n•\nMaintains a sensory buffer and perception history.\n•\nFor text input it stores type, content, timestamp, word count, question detection, sentiment, and simple entity extraction.\n•\nFor tool output it stores tool name, output content, timestamp, and success flag based on whether output contains error.\nPerception record structure\nperception = {\n\"type\": \"text_input\",\n\"content\": text,\n\"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n\"word_count\": len(text.split()),\n\"contains_question\": \"?\" in text,\n\"sentiment\": self._analyze_sentiment(text),\n\"entities\": self._extract_entities(text)\n}\n7.2 ReasoningModule and PlanningModule\n•\nReasoning constructs an LLM prompt asking what the user needs, what information exists/missing, constraints, and memory\npatterns.\n•\nIt assesses confidence by counting uncertainty markers such as might/maybe/unclear and confidence markers such as\nclearly/definitely.\n•\nPlanning asks the LLM for specific actions, order of operations, expected outcomes, fallback options, and success criteria.\n•\nIf execution fails, adapt_plan prompts the model to revise the plan using execution feedback.\nExam-important: Reasoning answers: what does this mean? Planning answers: what should we do next, in what order?\n7.3 ActionModule and tool selection\n•\nActionModule receives a plan, selects tools for steps, executes them, and records success/details.\n•\nTools in the example include WebSearch, Calculator, and MemorySearch.\n•\nTool selection is simplified keyword matching. Production agents should use more reliable routing and validation.\nTool set in the DOCX\nAvailable tools in CognitiveAgent._create_tools():\n- WebSearch: simulated search response\n- Calculator: evaluates math expressions safely enough for demo, with try/except\n- MemorySearch: retrieves relevant semantic memory\n7.4 LearningModule and MemorySystem\nMemory type\nPurpose in agent\nWorking memory\nImmediate conversation context.\nSummary memory\nCompressed recent history to preserve context without unlimited tokens.\nSemantic memory\nLong-term facts/knowledge stored and retrieved by embeddings/vector\nsearch.\nEpisodic memory\nSpecific experiences/interactions and outcomes.\nProcedural memory\nStrategies, tool effectiveness, and learned ways of doing tasks.",
              "image": "assets/pages/ai-ml-agentic-ai/page-023.webp",
              "keyPoints": [
                "Exam-important: Reasoning answers: what does this mean? Planning answers: what should we do next, in what order?"
              ]
