              "page": 24,
              "text": "Source page screenshot - DOCX page 29: memory architecture\nHow to read it: The page separates memory into specialized systems. Working memory handles immediate context; semantic memory stores facts; episodic\nmemory stores experiences; procedural memory stores learned strategies.\nExam-important: Memory is not one thing. Exam answers should separate working, semantic, episodic, and procedural memory.\n7.5 CognitiveAgent.process_input() end-to-end\nMain code flow\nprocess_input(user_input):\n1. Perceive input\n2. Retrieve relevant semantic and episodic memory\n3. Reason about situation and approach\n4. Create plan\n5. Execute plan with tools\n6. Adapt plan if execution fails\n7. Learn from interaction\n8. Update memory systems",
