              "text": "15. Quick revision cheat sheet\nHierarchy:\nAI -> Machine Learning -> Deep Learning -> Generative AI / LLMs\nLLM pipeline:\ntext -> tokens -> embeddings -> transformer -> next-token probabilities -> generated output\nMLP computation:\nh = f(W*x + b)\nTraining loop:\nforward pass -> loss -> backpropagation -> optimizer update -> repeat\nAgent loop:\nperceive -> reason -> plan -> act -> learn -> repeat\nCompare\nRemember\nClassification vs generation\nClassification labels an input; generation creates new content.\nPretraining vs fine-tuning\nPretraining learns general patterns; fine-tuning specializes.\nPrompting vs fine-tuning\nPrompting changes input; fine-tuning changes weights.\nMLP vs deep network\nMLP is a basic feedforward ANN; deep networks have multiple hidden\nlayers/architectures.\nBackpropagation vs gradient descent\nBackprop computes gradients; gradient descent uses gradients to update\nparameters.\nAgent vs chatbot\nAgent has goals, state, tools, planning, and feedback loops.\nLangChain vs LangGraph\nLangChain chains apps; LangGraph adds stateful cyclic graphs.\nAutoGen vs CrewAI\nAutoGen emphasizes agent conversations/code; CrewAI emphasizes\nroles/tasks/crews/process.",
