              "page": 6,
              "text": "CS496 Blockchain Module - Exam-Ready Inline Diagram Guide\nPage 6\nSlide image: relationship between blockchain and mining.\n1.11 Transaction lifecycle\n1 User/sender generates a transaction using wallet software or another interface.\n2 Wallet signs the transaction using the sender's private key.\n3 Transaction is broadcast to the blockchain network using flooding/gossip.\n4 Nodes verify the transaction and propagate it further.\n5 Mining nodes include transactions in candidate blocks.\n6 Mining starts once the previous block has been broadcast by the winning node.\n7 Miners compete to solve proof-of-work for their candidate block.\n8 The first successful miner broadcasts the confirmed block.\n9 Other nodes stop mining the old candidate and verify the winning block.\n10 Transactions in the valid block are added to the ledger.",
              "image": "assets/pages/blockchain/page-006.webp",
