              "id": "blockchain-t06-c01",
              "title": "5. Solidity by Example",
              "page": 22,
              "text": "5. Solidity by Example\n5.1 What Solidity is\nSolidity is a high-level, object-oriented smart contract language designed to target the Ethereum Virtual\nMachine. It is influenced by C++, Python, and JavaScript. The course document calls it a variant of\nJavaScript, but that is too narrow.\n5.2 Counter example\nThe Counter contract demonstrates a persistent state variable and functions that read/write it.\n5.3 Primitive data types\nType\nMeaning / range\nbool\ntrue or false; default false.\nuint8\nUnsigned integer from 0 to 2^8 - 1.\nuint16\nUnsigned integer from 0 to 2^16 - 1.\nuint256 / uint\nUnsigned integer from 0 to 2^256 - 1; uint is alias for uint256.\nint256 / int\nSigned integer from -2^255 to 2^255 - 1; int is alias for int256.\nint128\nSigned integer from -2^127 to 2^127 - 1.\naddress\nEthereum address; default is 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000.\nbytes1\nFixed-size one-byte value.\nbytes\nDynamic byte array; shorthand for byte[].\nSolidity provides type(int256).min and type(int256).max for minimum and maximum int256 values.\n5.4 Variable categories\nCategory\nWhere declared\nStored on-chain?\nLocal\nInside a function\nNo\nState\nAt contract level\nYes\nGlobal\nBuilt-in blockchain context variables such as block.timestamp and\nmsg.sender\nProvided by environment\nc o n t r a c t V a r i a b l e s {\ns t r i n g p u b l i c t e x t = \" H e l l o \" ;  / / s t a t e\nu i n t 2 5 6 p u b l i c n u m = 1 2 3 ;\n/ / s t a t e\nf u n c t i o n d o S o m e t h i n g ( ) p u b l i c v i e w {\nu i n t 2 5 6 i = 4 5 6 ;\n/ / l o c a l\nu i n t 2 5 6 t i m e s t a m p = b l o c k . t i m e s t a m p ;\na d d r e s s s e n d e r = m s g . s e n d e r ;\n}\n}\n5.5 Constants and immutables\nA constant is fixed at compile time. An immutable variable can be assigned once, usually in the\nconstructor, and then cannot be modified.\na d d r e s s p u b l i c c o n s t a n t M Y _ A D D R E S S = 0 x 7 7 7 7 8 8 8 8 9 9 9 9 A a A A b B b b C c c c d d D d e e e E f F F f C c C c ;\nu i n t 2 5 6 p u b l i c c o n s t a n t M Y _ U I N T = 1 2 3 ;\na d d r e s s p u b l i c i m m u t a b l e m y A d d r ;\nu i n t 2 5 6 p u b l i c i m m u t a b l e m y U i n t ;\nc o n s t r u c t o r ( u i n t 2 5 6 _ m y U i n t ) {\nm y A d d r = m s g . s e n d e r ;\nm y U i n t = _ m y U i n t ;\n}",
