              "text": "CS496 Blockchain Module - Exam-Ready Inline Diagram Guide\nPage 34\nFunction\nMeaning\nBonding / parachain auctions\nProjects bond DOT to win a parachain slot for a fixed period, usually up to two years in\nthe slide.\n9.5 Scalability and finality\nPolkadot improves scalability by processing transactions in parallel across multiple parachains. Each\nparachain operates independently instead of forcing all transactions through one global sequential chain.\nThe deck also says Polkadot uses advanced finality mechanisms to secure the Relay Chain.\n9.6 Benefits and advantages\nBenefit\nMeaning\nInteroperability\nDifferent blockchains can share information/assets.\nScalability\nMultiple parachains process transactions in parallel.\nShared security\nParachains benefit from Relay Chain security.\nCustomizability\nDevelopers can tailor blockchains for specific use cases.\nEcosystem development\nEncourages collaborative development and innovation.\nForkless upgrades\nNetwork can upgrade without disruptive hard forks.\nDemocratic governance\nCommunities can govern and evolve the network.\nSlide 8 is mislabeled \"Proof of History\". Its actual content is Polkadot benefits, not Solana PoH.\n9.7 Nominated Proof of Stake\nRole\nFunction\nValidators\nSecure the Relay Chain, validate parachain transactions, participate in consensus, and produce\nblocks.\nNominators\nStake DOT behind trustworthy validators, supporting network security.\nCollators\nManage parachain transactions and submit valid candidates to Relay Chain validators.\nFishermen\nMonitor and report misconduct.\nExam-important: Validators do core validation; nominators back validators with stake;\ncollators handle parachain transaction candidates; fishermen report bad behavior.\nPolkadot's official technical documentation describes a hybrid consensus model: BABE for block production and\nGRANDPA for provable finality. This is more detailed than the slide, but useful for correctness.",
