              "id": "blockchain-t11-c01",
              "title": "10. Key terms",
              "page": 36,
              "text": "10. Key terms\nTerm\nDefinition\nBlockchain\nAppend-only distributed ledger secured by cryptography and consensus.\nP2P network\nNetwork where peers share data without a central server.\nBlock\nContainer of transactions and metadata.\nBlock header\nMetadata used for linking, mining, and validation.\nHash\nFixed-size digest of data; small input changes cause major output changes.\nPrevious block hash\nHash pointer linking a block to its predecessor.\nMerkle root\nSingle root hash summarizing many data items.\nDigital signature\nCryptographic proof that a private-key holder authorized data.\nDouble spending\nAttempt to spend the same digital value twice.\nProof-of-work\nConsensus mechanism based on computational hash search.\nTarget\nMaximum acceptable hash value in PoW.\nDifficulty\nMeasure of how hard it is to find a valid PoW hash.\nNonce\nValue miners vary to search for valid hashes.\nUTXO\nUnspent Transaction Output; Bitcoin spendable unit.\nEOA\nExternally Owned Account; Ethereum account controlled by a private key.\nContract account\nEthereum account controlled by code.\nEVM\nEthereum Virtual Machine; executes smart contract bytecode.\nGas\nUnit measuring computation/storage effort in Ethereum.\nSolidity\nHigh-level smart contract language for EVM.\nABI\nInterface description used by apps to call contract bytecode.\nWei\nSmallest ETH denomination.\nValidator\nPoS participant that proposes and attests blocks.\nAttestation\nValidator vote supporting a block/checkpoint.\nFinality\nCondition where reverting a block would require severe economic/protocol penalties.\nLMD-GHOST\nEthereum fork-choice rule.\nCasper FFG\nEthereum finality gadget.\nRANDAO\nEthereum decentralized randomness mechanism.\nProof of History\nSolana cryptographic clock/order mechanism.\nTower BFT\nSolana BFT-style validator voting consensus described in the slides.\nRelay Chain\nPolkadot central chain providing coordination and shared security.\nParachain\nSpecialized chain connected to Polkadot Relay Chain.\nBridge\nConnection to external blockchains.\nNPoS\nPolkadot nominated proof-of-stake mechanism.",
