              "text": "11. Quick revision cheat sheet\nBitcoin\n● Bitcoin = P2P electronic cash.\n● Core problem solved = double spending without trusted third party.\n● Block header = version, previous hash, Merkle root, timestamp, difficulty bits, nonce.\n● PoW challenge = find header hash below target.\n● Lower target = higher difficulty.\n● Difficulty adjusts every 2,016 blocks toward a 10-minute average block interval.\n● Bitcoin uses UTXO model: inputs, outputs, change, fee.\n● Wallet manages keys and builds/signed transactions; it does not literally store coins.\n● Accepted chain = chain with most cumulative proof-of-work.\nEthereum\n● Ethereum = programmable blockchain for smart contracts and DApps.\n● EOA = private-key account; contract account = code-controlled account.\n● Account state = nonce, balance, storageRoot, codeHash.\n● EVM executes smart contract bytecode.\n● State writes cost gas; off-chain view calls can be free.\n● Historical PoW algorithm = Ethash, memory-hard with cache + DAG.\n● Ethereum moved to PoS on September 15, 2022.\n● PoS validator stake = 32 ETH.\n● Gasper = LMD-GHOST + Casper FFG.\n● Slot = 12 seconds; epoch = 32 slots.\nSolidity and smart contracts\n● Solidity variables: local, state, global.\n● uint = uint256; int = int256.\n● msg.sender = caller; block.timestamp = current block timestamp.\n● payable functions can receive ETH.\n● require() checks a condition and reverts on failure.\n● mapping(key => value) is not iterable and returns default values for unset keys.\n● Events are logs stored in transaction receipts.\n● ERC-20 = standard for fungible tokens.\nSolana\n● Goal = high throughput, low cost, low latency.\n● Uses PoS plus Proof of History.\n● PoH = cryptographic clock/order sequence, not full consensus alone.\n● Tower BFT = validator agreement/voting mechanism in the slides.\n● Firedancer = independent validator client/performance/client diversity.",
